  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>paneer</strong> into bite-sized cubes</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat and once hot, add the <strong>chopped paneer </strong>and cook for 2-3 min until it's browned on all sides</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the paneer has browned, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and cook for 5 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, crush your <strong>cardamom pods </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Melt a knob of <strong>butter</strong> in a pot with a matching lid over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>crushed cardamom pods </strong>and <strong>star anise</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>to the pot and cook for 1 min further, then add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has been absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>pilau rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>ground fenugreek</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if your pan is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the spices are cooking, dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[510ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> tomato stock </strong>to the pan, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it until it's wilted</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool enough to handle</p><p>Squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>chopped spinach</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further – this is your <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>paneer saag masala</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, chop most of your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Stir the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> through the <strong>pilau rice</strong>, discard the star anise and cardamom pods</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2393-Step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> fragrant paneer saag masala</strong> with the <strong>pilau rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
